sentences: Ta ei jätka seda teemat edasi.
context: The Estonian word 'jätkata' is a verb that means to continue, proceed, or carry on with something. It's an infinitive form of the verb and is commonly used in various contexts - continuing work, proceeding with a discussion, carrying on with activities. The conjugation would change depending on subject: ma jätkan (I continue), sa jäktad (you continue), ta jätkab (he/she/it continues) etc.
